	<h2 id="rabbits-info-heading">Basic info</h2>
	
	<p id="rabbits-info">Rabbits are small mammals in the family <em>Leporidae</em> of the order Lagomorpha <br>
		(along with the <strong>hare and the pika</strong>). Oryctolagus cuniculus includes the <br>
		European rabbit species and its descendants, the world's 305 breeds of <br>
		domestic rabbit. Sylvilagus includes <em><strong>13 wild rabbit species</em></strong>, among them <br>
		the seven types of cottontail.</p>
